  <summary date="2022-07-15T16:31:37Z" status="Introduced in House">Stop Mandating Additional Requirements for Travel Act or the SMART Act

This bill nullifies on July 4, 2021, the rule issued by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention on January 29, 2021, that requires the use of face masks on planes, trains, buses, and other public conveyances and at transportation hubs to prevent the transmission of COVID-19.</summary>
